<p>I am using SQL Server 2012 Full Text Search.</p>  <p>I have a field in "categories" table that contains main keywords of categories and i am using a separator character such as "-" or "," for each keyword.</p>  <p>This is a Persian sample of data for keyword field:</p>  <p>Persian Sample:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>,یراق الات پنجره,یراق الات درب و پنجره,یراق پنجره,</p> </blockquote>  <p>English Sample:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>,door,entry door,yard door,</p> </blockquote>  <p>Now when i use this "Like" statement, the result is OK:</p>  <pre><code>select * from  categories where  SiteSearchExactMacth like '%,درب,%' select * from  categories where  SiteSearchExactMacth like '%,door,%' </code></pre>  <p>But when i use FTS the result returns more than records of "Like" query and "," or "-" character will be ignored:</p>  <pre><code>select * from  categories where contains( SiteSearchExactMacth ,N'",درب,"') select * from  categories where contains( SiteSearchExactMacth ,N'",door,"') </code></pre>  <p>How can i use Full Text Search for this case?</p>